President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Maura Connelly as the Ambassador to the Republic of Lebanon, Daniel B. Smith as the Ambassador to the Hellenic Republic, and Subra Suresh as the Director of the National Science Foundation. Maura Connelly is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as a Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Bureau of Near Eastern Affairs. Daniel B. Smith is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Executive Secretary of the State Department. Subra Suresh is currently the Dean of the School of Engineering at MIT and has extensive experience in materials science and engineering.